<dl id="n56187e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n56" href="#n56187e">N56 (VI.B.41)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n56all.htm#n56187e"> 187(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Steamboat Bill</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The Leightons, who wrote <mark><i>Steamboat Bill</i></mark>, which is the <i>Casey Jones</i> of water travel, are sometimes credited with the author of the railroad classic as well, and Joe Cook believes they evolved it from an authentic folk-song. <small> Sigmund Spaeth, <a name="REAW3" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#REAW3"><cite title="source">Read 'Em and Weep</cite></a> (1935) 119n</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
